</game> ','F.E.A.R. is a psychological horror first-person shooter from 2005. On August 17, 2006, F.E.A.R.''s multiplayer component was retitled F.E.A.R. Combat and made available for free download; owners of both editions can play together. The multiplayer includes deathmatch, team deathmatch, capture the flag, last man standing, control, and conquer all game modes. Additionally, some of the game''s modes have a "SlowMo" variant that allows players to make a modified use of the reflex time effect from the singleplayer.','../../icons/234.png');
Insert into GAMETRACE.GAME (GAMEID,GAMENAME,GAMEPC,GAMERY,GAMEPSEC,GAMEPMIN,GAMEPHOUR,GAMEPDAY,GAMEPN,GIMG,GAMEDR,GAMEDESC,GAMEICON) values (1392,'Grandia II',0,2002,0,0,0,0,0,'../../games/1392.jpg','<game>
